t his feet, und so weiter. Stop short, you people—I raise a huge white palm like a German policeman, stop! No sighs of compassion, people, none whatever. Stop, pity! I do not accept your sympathy; for among you there are sure to be a few souls who will pity me—me, a poet misunderstood. “Mist, vapor … in the mist a chord that quivers.” No, that’s not verse, that’s from old Dusty’s great book, Crime and Slime. Sorry: Schuld und Sühne (German edition). Any remorse on my part is abs